title: 2016 Burton US Open CLIF Best Trick – Hannah Teter, Halfpipe
description: Going retro in the Burton US Open Halfpipe Finals, Hannah Teter used her first hit on the third run to throw this backside indie to win the CLIF Raise the Bar Award . CLIF challenges athletes to “Raise the Bar” with awards for best throwback and most progressive tricks. Awarded in both halfpipe and slopestyle with a $10,000 total prize purse up for grabs.
